<br>
Let's back up for a second.  Ultimately, the guild's responsibility is keeping the guild's ability to function at a premium.<br>
<br>
A loot item exists that is good for several classes, but is exceedingly good for one specific role.  A player of a different but usable class camps the item. The guild is required for the takedown. The guild should decide where it benefits the guild, not auto-award to the player just because they camped it. Especially if that player has a record of non-attendance (17% sounds low for a heavy raiding guild).<br>
<br>
This isn't about Tindi screwing over a member, this is about a member having unreal expectations.  Granted, someone should have told Phytir like 2 months ago that it likely wouldn't goto him.<br>
<br>
Let me try a different perspective, Lukieb.  I camp Nagafens lair waiting for Nagafen, so I can get a CoF. I am in your guild. When he spawns I ask the guild to come kill him, should I expect to get a CoF?<br>
